observations.recommendation:
We reiterated prior year’s recommendation that Management:

(1) Revert to the Cash-in Bank, Current Account, of the General Fund the balance of the Time Deposits upon its maturity, after deducting the balance of the Share from National Wealth which shall be transferred to a Trust Fund account in the General Fund, in order that the same may be appropriated and used in the implementation of various PPAs that will benefit the constituents;

(2) Utilize the proceeds from the Share from National Wealth strictly in accordance with its purpose pursuant to Section 294 of RA 7160; 

(3) Further, the Municipal Accountant shall certify that the funds intended to be placed in a time deposit are essentially idle after regular and recurring operating expenses within the context of the LGU’s cash operating cycle; and

(4) Henceforth, secure prior authority from the SB and the approval of the Local Chief Executive before placement of idle funds under the General Fund in HYSA or Time Deposit accounts.

We recommended that Management:
Ensure full coordination with other government agencies, among others, including the community and private utilities, to achieve effective and more synchronized planning and implementation of programs and projects;
Impose liquidated damages on the contractors for every day of delay; and initiate termination/rescission of contract on infrastructure projects when liquidated damages reaches 10% and negative slippages of more than 15% arising from contractor’s fault or negligence, pursuant to Section 68 and Annex I, of the Revised IRR of RA 9184.
Consider disqualification and/or blacklisting of contractors, and initiate the immediate take-over process of terminated projects to facilitate completion of the projects within the project timeframe; and
Henceforth, minimize the delays in project implementation by:
Conscientiously carrying out the detailed engineering to ensure that issues such as viability of the project sites are properly addressed during the feasibility or preliminary engineering study prior to project implementation;
Thoroughly review and evaluate the Program of Work to ensure that project designs and estimates are properly prepared and that all phases of the projects are covered to minimize variation orders and time extensions which often resulted in the increase of project cost and delayed completion;
Direct the BAC to properly verify and evaluate during post- qualification the operating conditions of equipment and other construction requirements, among others, to ensure adequacy, availability and suitability of the contractor’s technical capability; and strictly monitoring and supervising the projects implemented by the LGU

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) institutionalize the PSCP by creating a working group that will perform the following activities:
to conduct risk assessment;
to identify critical processes and functions;
to determine scenarios that may disrupt normal operation;
to conduct risk analysis and impact analysis;
to formulate the PSCP based on the identified risks on critical processes and functions and its related steps to be followed to eliminate, if not mitigate, the impact of the determined disruptions following the prescribed template and be guided by the PSCP guidebook; and
to submit plan to the MDRRMO for review, to the LCE for approval, and to the Sangguniang Bayan for the passage of a resolution to institutionalize the PSCP.
Further, we recommended that members of the working group be capacitated by allowing them to attend seminars/trainings on the formulation of the PSCP.

We reiterated our previous year’s recommendation that Management:
Pursue the immediate approval of the Ten-Year ESWMP as required under R.A. No. 9003 to ensure its sustainability, effectiveness and relevance in relation to local and international progress in the area of Solid Waste Management;
Properly supervise the maintenance of all Material Recovery Facilities in all the Barangays of the Municipality to achieve its purpose of ensuring the cleanliness of the entire community.

