We recommended that Management:

Direct the Municipal Accountant submit the monthly accounts and financial reports on or before the deadlines;

Require the concerned AOs to submit the accounts and financial reports to the Municipal Treasurer on or before the 3rd day of the month, who shall thereafter submit the same to the MAO for recording on or before the fifth day of the ensuing month;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to strictly comply with the timelines on the submission of accounts to the Auditor within the first ten days of the ensuing month;

Look into the possibility of augmenting the Municipal Accountant’s Office with personnel from other departments, especially during report preparation periods and/or allowing them to render overtime, subject to availability of funds, in order to submit the accounts and financial reports on the mandated deadlines; and

Initiate the necessary administrative and/or criminal action in case of unjustified failure/refusal to effect compliance with the foregoing requirements by subordinate officials.

