To ensure proper accounting and promote better control in the receipt and issuance of Supplies and Materials, we recommended for the Local Chief Executive to require:
The MGSO to maintain perpetual inventory records of Supplies and Materials purchased and to ensure that complete records of the items issued to requisitioning departments/offices are kept. At the end of each month, she shall prepare the monthly Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued, a copy of which shall be furnished the Municipal Accountant for recording;
The Municipal Accountant to record all Purchases of Supplies and Materials under the proper inventory account following the perpetual inventory method;
At the end of each semester, the MGSO shall conduct a physical inventory, in coordination with the concerned department/office, of all unused Supplies and Materials and shall prepare a consolidated inventory report thereon and furnish the Municipal Accountant a copy thereof; and
The Municipal Accountant to take up the necessary adjustment, if any, in the respective inventory and expense accounts for Supplies and Materials based on the consolidated inventory report provided by the Property Officer.

We recommended the following:
Management to constitute an Inventory Committee headed by the Municipal Engineer that shall conduct the inventory of the local roads under the jurisdiction of the Municipality.  A Report on the Physical count of the Road Networks System shall be prepared copy furnished the Municipal Accountant and the MGSO;
The MGSO to: (b.1) Render a Report on Local Road Network and Road Map; and, (b.2) Keep a complete and updated Local Road Network Property Card (LRNPCs) for all roads and its components;
The Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the MGSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and
The Municipal Accountant to: (d.1) Prepare the Journal Entry Voucher to record the beginning balance of the Local Road Network and its components; (d.2) Prepare and maintain LRNLCs; (d.3) Keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network; and (d.4) Prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year.

